HEADWORD: Acetylene
<hw>A*cet"y*lene</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A gaseous compound of carbon and hydrogen, in the proportion of two
atoms of the former to two of the latter. It is a colorless gas, with a
peculiar, unpleasant odor, and is produced for use as an illuminating
gas in a number of ways, but chiefly by the action of water on calcium
carbide. Its light is very brilliant.</def> <rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

